quran[29]{c,v,t}:
  7,88,"The elite of his people who were arrogant said, ‘O Shu'ayb, we will surely expel you and the faithful who are with you from our town, or else you shall revert to our creed.’ He said, ‘What! Even if we should be unwilling"
  7,89,"We would be fabricating a lie against Allah should we revert to your creed after Allah had delivered us from it. It does not behoove us to return to it, unless Allah, our Lord, should wish so. Our Lord embraces all things in [His] knowledge. In Allah we have put our trust.’ ‘Our Lord! Judge justly between us and our people, and You are the best of judges!’"
  7,90,"The elite of his people who were faithless said, ‘If you follow Shu'ayb, you will indeed be losers.’"
  7,91,"So the earthquake seized them, and they lay lifeless prostrate in their homes"
  7,92,Those who impugned Shu'ayb became as if they had never lived there. Those who impugned Shu‘ayb were themselves the losers
  7,93,"So he abandoned them [to their fate] and said, ‘O my people! Certainly, I communicated to you the messages of my Lord, and I was your well-wisher. So how should I grieve for a faithless lot?’"
  7,94,"We did not send a prophet to any town without visiting its people with stress and distress so that they might entreat [for Allah’s forgiveness]"
  7,95,"Then We changed the ill [conditions] to good until they multiplied [in numbers] and said, ‘Adversity and ease befell our fathers [too].’ Then We seized them suddenly while they were unaware"
  7,96,"If the people of the towns had been faithful and Godwary, We would have opened to them blessings from the heaven and the earth. But they denied; so We seized them because of what they used to earn"
  7,97,Do the people of the towns feel secure from Our punishment overtaking them at night while they are asleep
  7,98,Do the people of the towns feel secure from Our punishment overtaking them at midday while they are playing around
  7,99,Do they feel secure from Allah’s devising? No one feels secure from Allah’s devising except the people who are losers
  7,100,"Does it not dawn upon those who inherited the earth after its [former] inhabitants that if We wish We will punish them for their sins, and set a seal on their hearts so they would not hear"
  7,101,"These are the towns some of whose accounts We recount to you. Their apostles certainly brought them manifest proofs, but they were not the ones to believe in what they had denied earlier. Thus does Allah put a seal on the hearts of the faithless"
  7,102,"We did not find in most of them any [loyalty to] covenants. Indeed, We found most of them to be transgressors"
  7,103,"Then after them We sent Moses with Our signs to Pharaoh and his elite, but they wronged them. So observe how was the fate of the agents of corruption"
  7,104,"And Moses said, ‘O Pharaoh, I am indeed an apostle from the Lord of all the worlds"
  7,105,It behooves me to say nothing about Allah except the truth. I certainly bring you a manifest proof from your Lord. So let the Children of Israel go with me.’
  7,106,"He said, ‘If you have brought a sign, produce it, should you be truthful.’"
  7,107,"Thereat he threw down his staff, and behold, it became a manifest python"
  7,108,"Then he drew out his hand, and behold, it was white to the onlookers"
  7,109,"The elite of Pharaoh’s people said, ‘This is indeed an expert magician"
  7,110,he seeks to expel you from your land.’ ‘So what do you advise?’
  7,111,"They said, ‘Put him and his brother off for a while, and send heralds to the cities"
  7,112,to bring you every expert magician.’
  7,113,"And the magicians came to Pharaoh. They said, ‘We shall indeed have a reward if we were to be the victors?’"
  7,114,"He said, ‘Of course! And indeed you shall be among those near [to me].’"
  7,115,"They said, ‘O Moses, will you throw [first], or shall we throw?’"
  7,116,"He said, ‘Throw [yours].’ So when they threw, they bewitched the people’s eyes and overawed them, producing a tremendous magic"